               <desc type="building-data" xml:lang="en">
                  <p source="#bibl000211-2" xml:lang="en">The <placeName>Longxing
                        Monastery</placeName> Zhuanlunzang Pavilion (zhuanlunzang ge 轉輪藏閣) is a
                     two-story pavilion named for the revolving cabinet for storing Buddhist sutras
                     (zhuanlunzang <term>轉輪藏</term>) inside of it. The zhuanlunzang pavilion is
                     located on the west side of the courtyard in front of the <placeName
                        ref="/place/000064c">Dabei Pavilion</placeName>, facing east. The building
                     is three bays wide and three bays deep, with a single-bay wide roofed portico
                     (described as either baosha <term>抱厦</term> or fujie <term>副階</term>) along the
                     front (Guo 2009, 380-85; Hebei sheng Zhengding xian wenwu baoguansuo 2000,
                     15-16). It adopts a single-eaves, hip-gable <term ref="/keyword/k000185"
                        >歇山</term> (aka jiuji <term>九脊</term> "nine-ridge" or shaliangtou <term
                        ref="/keyword/k000185">厦兩頭</term>), roof and both upper and lower pillars
                     display rise (shengqi <term>生起</term>) toward the corners and inward incline
                     (cejiao <term ref="/keyword/k000006">侧脚</term>). The building design is
                     described as falling between the diange 殿閣/diantang <term
                        ref="/keyword/k000130">殿堂</term> and tingtang <term ref="/keyword/k000129"
                        >廳堂</term> styles as described in Yingzao Fashi 營造法式 (Guo 2009, 380-85).
                     There are three types of pillars used, including the portico pillars (fujiezhu
                        <term>副階柱</term>), eaves pillars (yanzhu <term ref="/keyword/k000111"
                        >檐柱</term>), and inner pillars (neizhu <term>内柱</term>), all of which are
                     circular. The pillars are supported by simple upturned basin-style bases 素覆盆式柱礎
                     (Zhengdingxian wenwu baoguansuo 2000, 15-16).</p>
                  <p source="#bibl000211-2" xml:lang="en">In the center of the lower level of this
                     pavilion is a timber revolving sutra cabinet (zhuanlunzang <term>轉輪藏</term>),
                     which is a rotating bookshelf for sacred texts, such as the tripitaka (sanzang 三藏). It
                     appears to have been built in accordance with the guidelines for revolving
                     scripture cabinets as described in the small woodwork (xiaomuzuo <term
                        ref="/keyword/k000231">小木作</term>) section in the Yingzao fashi <term
                        ref="https://tinyurl.com/ynbn8e6b">營造法式</term> (1103) (Zhengdingxian wenwu
                     baoguansuo 2000, 15-6). Its plan is a regular octagon, with a pivot set at the
                     center. A frame is built into the large wooden structure of the building to
                     secure the position of the pivot. When pushed from the bottom, the revolving
                     cabinet can rotate freely (Guo 2009, 380-85). This is a rare extant example of
                     small woodwork from the Song Dynasty (Zhengdingxian wenwu baoguansuo 2000,
                     15-16).</p>
                  <p source="#bibl000211-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant"
                        ><placeName>隆興寺</placeName>轉輪藏閣是一座二層樓閣，以內部收藏經文的轉輪藏而得名。轉輪藏閣位於<placeName
                        ref="/place/000064c"
                        >大悲閣</placeName>的西南側，朝向東。建築寬度為三開間，進深為三開間，前部帶有<term>抱廈</term>/<term>副階</term>
                     (郭 2009， 380-85；河北省正定縣文物保管所 2000，15-16)
                        。建築採用單簷<term>九脊</term>頂，上下層柱子均帶有生起和<term ref="/keyword/k000006"
                        >侧脚</term>。屋頂形式介於《營造法式》（1103）所定的殿閣/<term ref="/keyword/k000130"
                        >殿堂</term>與<term ref="/keyword/k000129">廳堂</term>之間（郭
                        2009，380-85）。對於柱子的使用分為三種，包括<term>副階柱</term>、<term ref="/keyword/k000111"
                        >檐柱</term>和<term>內柱</term>，均為圓形。柱子下方均使用素覆盆式柱基來支撐（河北省正定縣文物保管所
                     2000，15-16）。</p>
                  <p source="#bibl000211-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant"
                        >此閣的底層正中央放置了一個木製轉輪藏，即一個用於收藏經文的旋轉書架。該書架是根據<term ref="/keyword/k000074"
                        >宋代</term>的《<term ref="https://tinyurl.com/ynbn8e6b"
                     >營造法式</term>》中關於轉輪藏的制度所建造的（河北省正定縣文物保管所
                     2000，15-16）。平面呈現正八邊形，中心設有軸心，上端搭建在建築的大木結構上，限定了軸心的位置。當受到推動力時，底端便可旋轉（郭
                        2009，380-85）。這座轉輪藏堪稱是宋代<term subtype="keyword" ref="/keyword/k000231"
                        >小木作</term>中的稀有文物（河北省正定縣文物保管所 2000，15-16）。</p>
